     SECTION 2: WHY THIS AREA
================================================ -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">The quiet bayside suburb that families and retirees pursue when Manly is beyond reach, with water access, Lota Creek foreshore, and a settled lifestyle character that is hard to replicate.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Lota sits approximately seventeen kilometres east of the Brisbane CBD, nestled between Manly and Wynnum in Brisbane's bayside corridor. The suburb is defined by its proximity to the water, its quiet residential streets, and its position as the compelling alternative for buyers who want the bayside lifestyle that Manly represents but find the most sought-after Manly addresses beyond their budget. Those buyers arrive in Lota having already researched the corridor. They know the bayside lifestyle, they have walked Cambridge Parade in Manly, they have checked the school catchments, and they have concluded that Lota delivers the waterside character they are looking for.
    </p>
